.SH NAME
lookit-serve - Start the web server


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlookit serve [path] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Start a web server for browsing markdown and code in a browser. Renders
markdown with GitHub Flavored Markdown, emoji, and syntax highlighting.
Watches for file changes and pushes live updates via Server-Sent Events.

.PP
API endpoints:
  /\fBapi/files?q=term   Fuzzy file search (JSON)
  /\fPapi/search?q=term  Full-text content search (JSON)
  /__api/graph          Link graph data (JSON)
  /graph                Interactive link graph visualization

.PP
The server adds security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options),
ETag caching, and skips auto-opening the browser when an SSH session is detected.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--css\fP=""
	path to custom CSS file

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for serve

.PP
\fB--no-https\fP[=false]
	disable HTTPS even if certs exist

.PP
\fB--open\fP[=false]
	open browser after starting

.PP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--port\fP=0
	server port


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB-c\fP, \fB--config\fP=""
	config file path

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	enable verbose logging

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	disable colors (ascii theme)

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	color theme (light|dark|auto|ascii)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  lookit serve
  lookit serve --port 3000 --open ~/docs
  lookit serve --css ./custom.css
  lookit serve --no-https
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBlookit(1)\fP


